cal, writes Steinberg. Political constitutions, as a form of beginning, imply the eventuality of their own renewals and their own reconstitutions. Motivated in part by recent reactionary insurgencies in the US, Europe, and Israel, this astute work of intellectual history posits the critique of myths of origin as a key principle of democratic government, affect, and citizenship, of their endurance as well as their fragility.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDemocracyxPhilosophy. 0aExodus, The. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh  aAbraham Lincoln.  aDemocracy.  aExile.  aFreud.  aHannah Arendt.  aIsrael.  aMoses.  aRace.  aReconstitutions.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107664860 cprintz978150363114440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363230140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503632301423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503632301/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DKUb2022